    <prp:abstract>We propose an ALMA observation of possible powerful AGN-driven winds in the Type II QSO at z=2.94, selected in the XMM-COSMOS survey. With z=2.94, [CII] 158 micron line is redshifted to Band 8 and our aim is to measure the line profile. This X-ray selected galaxy hosts an heavily obscured active nucleus with a high accretion rate, which is likely to drive a powerful AGN-driven wind to clear the surrounding shrouds. Together with the intense star formation with ~1400 Msun/yr, this object belongs to the class of Hyper-luminous infrared galaxies. Strong far-infrared emission-line of [CII] is expected, and if a galaxy-wide feedback due to the AGN-driven wind is operating, then its line profile would be distorted, which we aim to measure. With the multi-wavelngth datasets of COSMOS, XID147 is found to be one of the ideal target at the right epoch of the cosmic history (z~3) to search for observational signatures of AGN feedback at work.</prp:abstract>
